lines.filename: 1-D.Va-00000005F126.0B2-I heard you're a good dancer. You should try to beat my high score in Dance Floor!.mp3

lines.speaker: Symmetra
lines.filename: 2-Symmetra-00000005F10B.0B2-Have you checked the scoreboard recently_.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 3-D.Va-0000000640CD.0B2-(gasp) You didn't...!.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-00000005EC00.0B2-You're crazy strong, Zarya! How many of me could you lift_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 2-Zarya-00000005EC01.0B2-With or without the mech_.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-000000061613.0B2-I bet you're a pro at bowling.mp3

lines.speaker: Wrecking Ball
lines.filename: 2-Wrecking Ball-000000062625.0B2-(hamster noises) The hamster says, _No comment._.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 3-D.Va-000000061615.0B2-Aw! Who am I going to go with now_.mp3

lines.speaker: Wrecking Ball
lines.filename: 4-Wrecking Ball-000000062626.0B2-(hamster noises) Tuesdays are usually free.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-000000061617.0B2-You should visit me in Korea, Lena.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-000000061F7D.0B2-I'd love that!.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 3-D.Va-000000061619.0B2-I'll show you true hospitality, Korea style.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 4-Tracer-000000061F7E.0B2-I smell shenanigans. Sign me up!.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-00000006161B.0B2-We should get Ganymede to scout for us!.mp3

lines.speaker: Bastion
lines.filename: 2-Bastion-000000062BF7.0B2-(worried beeps).mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 3-D.Va-00000006161D.0B2-Don't worry! No one will touch a feather on Gany's head while Hana Song is here!.mp3

lines.speaker: Bastion
lines.filename: 4-Bastion-000000062BF8.0B2-(relieved beeps).mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-000000062394.0B2-How can you be good at shooting in real life but so bad in games_.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-000000061929.0B2-Not the same thing, I guess.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 3-D.Va-000000062395.0B2-(sighs) It's lonely at the top.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 4-Tracer-00000006192B.0B2-I can beat you at the cooking games though!.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-000000062398.0B2-Some day, I'm going to finally travel the world! Got any tips_.mp3

lines.speaker: Mei
lines.filename: 2-Mei-000000061CB2.0B2-Um...Travel light. But you never know when you need more socks! And underwear. And shirts. Oh, and pants.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-000000062DBA.0B2-Can't they get anything done without us_.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 2-Kiriko-000000062FA7.0B2-It's a full-time job being the capable ones.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-0000000640CA.0B2-Massive bomb-shatter!.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-000000064074.0B2-I still say _shatter-bomb_ has a better ring to it.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-0000000640CB.0B2-Can Volskaya's mechs do that_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 2-Zarya-0000000648CA.0B2-Hah. Not yet.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-0000000640CE.0B2-You don't look so good. Maybe you should sit this one out and leave the kills to me!.mp3

lines.speaker: Reaper
lines.filename: 2-Reaper-000000063850.0B2-I'll be fine once you shut up.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 1-D.Va-000000069B95.0B2-Feels nice not to be the shortest person on the team anymore.mp3

lines.speaker: Illari
lines.filename: 2-Illari-000000066DAC.0B2-I'm taller than you, and you know it.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 3-D.Va-000000069B92.0B2-Hmm... Your hair doesn't count!.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000041422.0B2-I hope the girl gave you more than a new coat of paint.mp3

lines.speaker: Orisa
lines.filename: 2-Orisa-0000000352AA.0B2-You may be surprised. I have received a number of upgrades since that battle.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000041466.0B2-You don't take a hint, do you Reinhardt_.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-00000004A602.0B2-And you don't know to stay down when you're beaten.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000041442.0B2-Symmetra... I am familiar with your work. I look forward to seeing it in person.mp3

lines.speaker: Symmetra
lines.filename: 2-Symmetra-000000043E96.0B2-Should I be worried_ I heard you leveled skyscrapers.mp3

lines.speaker: Symmetra
lines.filename: 3-Symmetra-000000043E97.0B2-My purpose is to create order. You are the embodiment of chaos.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000049C87.0B2-You disappoint me, Hanzo. With Talon, you could truly fulfill your destiny.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-0000000441D4.0B2-Find another errand boy, Akande.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000041444.0B2-Watch my back out there, Lacroix.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-000000043BA2.0B2-Tell me what needs to be done, and I will do it.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000041445.0B2-Retirement suits you.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-000000044482.0B2-And I think a hammer upside your face would suit you.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000041293.0B2-Hanzo, you should consider joining us. I think we'd see eye to eye.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-000000036045.0B2-I would have little to gain from such an arrangement. No, I will find my own path.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000041443.0B2-Ana Amari. I hate to see your talents wasted.mp3

lines.speaker: Ana
lines.filename: 2-Ana-000000043E61.0B2-That is the story of my life.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000041430.0B2-I thought I'd taken care of you. You're more resilient than you look.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-00000004B0EC.0B2-I've come back from worse.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000041292.0B2-Human strength will only get you so far.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 2-Zarya-00000002A7FF.0B2-True strength is hard work and dedication. Not augmentation.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000624DA.0B2-Why did the chicken cross the road_.mp3

lines.speaker: Junkrat
lines.filename: 2-Junkrat-00000006098E.0B2-Why_.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 3-Brigitte-0000000625C6.0B2-Why_.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 4-Doomfist-0000000624DB.0B2-Because to stagnate is to die. Never forget that.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000624E9.0B2-I hope this iteration of Overwatch proves more durable than the last.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 2-Sojourn-000000062671.0B2-If I were you, I'd be more worried about what's going to happen to Talon.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-00000005E9D2.0B2-How does one so young become Korea's strongest warrior_.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 2-D.Va-00000005E9D3.0B2-I'm the best. That's all you need to know.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 3-Doomfist-00000005E9D1.0B2-(laugh) Confidence! Let's hope it's not unfounded.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000624F1.0B2-Even past your prime, you are more lethal than ever.mp3

lines.speaker: Ana
lines.filename: 2-Ana-000000062515.0B2-Some people improve with age. Others never quite learn to keep their mouths shut.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000624F4.0B2-Your new weapons are impressive, but you lack the strength to wield them.mp3

lines.speaker: Orisa
lines.filename: 2-Orisa-000000062537.0B2-Efi made me kind. She did not make me weak.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000624F5.0B2-A claw hand_ Inefficient.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-000000061224.0B2-Well we can't all have ultra powerful gauntlets.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 3-Doomfist-0000000624F6.0B2-No, you cannot.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000624F7.0B2-You didn’t fail Overwatch, Cassidy. Overwatch failed you.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-00000006226C.0B2-I’m pretty sure it was mutual.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000624F8.0B2-Overwatch again, Cassidy_ Haven’t they proven unworthy of your talents_.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-00000006226D.0B2-It’s that or spend the rest of my life passed out in various diners.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 3-Doomfist-0000000624F9.0B2-There are other options.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 4-Cassidy-00000006226E.0B2-Sorry, uh. Talon’s my third choice.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000624FA.0B2-Has the child reconsidered my offer_ She would thrive with Talon's resources.mp3

lines.speaker: Orisa
lines.filename: 2-Orisa-00000006253D.0B2-You stand for everything wrong in this world. Efi will never join you.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 3-Doomfist-0000000624FB.0B2-If she cannot comprehend the era that awaits us, then perhaps I have no use for her after all.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000644CD.0B2-Who taught you the blade_.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-000000063C1E.0B2-The best swordmaster in the world.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 3-Doomfist-0000000644CE.0B2-Ah… her.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000644C5.0B2-The Circuit Royal. A contest of will and technical ingenuity. A dance of beauty... and destruction.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 2-Lúcio-000000064221.0B2-Is everything poetry and philosophy with you_.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 3-Doomfist-0000000644C6.0B2-Everything is, when you pay attention.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000644C8.0B2-You were truly fearsome in your prime.mp3

lines.speaker: Ana
lines.filename: 2-Ana-0000000640F8.0B2-I wanted respect, not fear.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-0000000644CA.0B2-The Shimada could rise again, if you so choose.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-000000063919.0B2-There is nothing to that name but pain.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 3-Doomfist-0000000644CB.0B2-Pain... and a sleeping dragon. Wake him up.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-00000006447D.0B2-You and Reyes were both enhanced soldiers. Yet he reached his full potential and you.mp3

lines.speaker: Soldier_ 76
lines.filename: 2-Soldier_ 76-000000063F0B.0B2-I wouldn't say he's thriving.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 3-Doomfist-00000006447E.0B2-Hmm... are you_.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-00000006447F.0B2-Cover me.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-000000063FDF.0B2-When have I not_.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000064480.0B2-You know the plan.mp3

lines.speaker: Reaper
lines.filename: 2-Reaper-000000063851.0B2-Leave no one alive.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000065D8A.0B2-You are bold to stand against Vishkar on your own.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 2-Lifeweaver-00000006625F.0B2-I'm not alone! The scientific community is on my side.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 3-Doomfist-000000065D8B.0B2-It would be wise not to count on that for long.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-00000006835C.0B2-You seem lost. Searching for your place in the world_.mp3

lines.speaker: Illari
lines.filename: 2-Illari-000000068C8C.0B2-No. I wouldn't know where to look.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 3-Doomfist-00000006835D.0B2-Embrace your inner conflict, and like-minded people will find you.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 1-Doomfist-000000066601.0B2-Where was this courage when Automaton was taken_.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 2-Lúcio-000000066602.0B2-Look, giving up the good life is a big sacrifice, okay_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-00000005A938.0B2-Winston, have you ever noticed any similarities between Athena and me_.mp3

lines.speaker: Winston
lines.filename: 2-Winston-00000005BCDE.0B2-Uh... you both have a... dry sense of humor.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-00000005A939.0B2-Perhaps that is programming we share.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-000000060A34.0B2-You know, I saved Cole's life once.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe
lines.filename: 2-Ashe-00000005B9CB.0B2-Am I supposed to be thankful for that_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-00000005D6B4.0B2-Why did you choose the name _Null Sector_.mp3

lines.speaker: Ramattra
lines.filename: 2-Ramattra-00000005D4B7.0B2-Because we defy the numbers humans gave us. We are zeroes, undefined.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-00000005D6B5.0B2-Is that not its own struggle_.mp3

lines.speaker: Ramattra
lines.filename: 4-Ramattra-00000005D4B8.0B2-Of course. I expect you know that better than anyone.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-00000005E583.0B2-That broadcast said humans oppressed omnics here. Is that true_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 2-Sojourn-00000005E5A4.0B2-Yeah, it is.mp3

lines.speaker: Claire
lines.filename: 3-Claire-00000005E590.0B2-Um, yeah.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 4-Echo-00000005E5A5.0B2-I see. Are things better now_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 5-Sojourn-00000005E582.0B2-Sometimes.mp3

lines.speaker: Claire
lines.filename: 6-Claire-00000005E596.0B2-Better than most of the world.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-00000005E595.0B2-Why do you think the omnics aren't fighting back, Captain_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 2-Sojourn-00000005E592.0B2-They weren't made for war, Echo. You're, uh.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-00000005E593.0B2-Improved_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 4-Sojourn-00000005E59B.0B2-Different. I was going to say _different_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-00000005E9D4.0B2-If you'd like, I could train with you. Facing yourself can help you improve.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 2-D.Va-00000005E9D5.0B2-Oh, finally! A balanced 1v1!.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000616C0.0B2-Thank you Torbjorn. I've learned much from observing you.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-000000061227.0B2-Well I'm known to be an excellent teacher.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-0000000616BE.0B2-Yes, I believe I've grasped what not to do in stressful situations.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 4-Torbjörn-000000061229.0B2-You shouldn't believe everything Mercy says, y'know.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000614F1.0B2-I have been studying the composition of your songs.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 2-Lúcio-00000006236D.0B2-Studying_ Nah, you've got to feel and enjoy the music!.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-0000000614F3.0B2-I enjoy the mathematics.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000614F4.0B2-Cole Cassidy, Cole Cassidy, Cole Cassidy.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-0000000622A2.0B2-You called_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-0000000614F6.0B2-I just like saying your name, that's all.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000614F7.0B2-I think I can pull off a cowboy hat.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-0000000622A3.0B2-Want me to buy you one_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-0000000614F9.0B2-No need. I'll just borrow yours.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000614FA.0B2-Could you describe the taste of chicken rice_.mp3

lines.speaker: Mei
lines.filename: 2-Mei-0000000623CA.0B2-Oh, it's very tender and tasty but... subtle_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-0000000614FC.0B2-Thank you. It was Dr. Liao's favorite dish.mp3

lines.speaker: Mei
lines.filename: 4-Mei-0000000623CB.0B2-I'll have some and explain it better next time!.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000614FE.0B2-Hana, what does kimchi taste like_.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 2-D.Va-00000006238F.0B2-It's salty and spicy and garlicky! (sigh) It's yummy fried too!.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-000000061500.0B2-Fried_ Interesting!.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 4-D.Va-000000062390.0B2-Aw, now I'm hungry!.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000626A9.0B2-Any luck getting past my fourth firewall yet_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sombra
lines.filename: 2-Sombra-000000061C4D.0B2-Already done. Your fifth's tricky though.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-0000000626AA.0B2-Do you want a hint_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sombra
lines.filename: 4-Sombra-000000061C4F.0B2-(offended scoff) Don't you dare.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-000000061502.0B2-You are not alone.mp3

lines.speaker: Soldier_ 76
lines.filename: 2-Soldier_ 76-000000062F5F.0B2-I don't need your pity.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-000000061504.0B2-It's not pity. I know how it feels to be alone for a long time.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-000000061505.0B2-Is peanut butter that delicious_.mp3

lines.speaker: Winston
lines.filename: 2-Winston-0000000620DD.0B2-It's peanuty buttery heaven!.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-000000061507.0B2-But my analysis shows me it's high in trans saturated fats.mp3

lines.speaker: Winston
lines.filename: 4-Winston-0000000620DE.0B2-Did Athena put you up to this_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-00000006150B.0B2-May I borrow your copy of Thucydides's History sometime_.mp3

lines.speaker: Wrecking Ball
lines.filename: 2-Wrecking Ball-000000062623.0B2-(hamster noises) Unfortunately, that is not possible.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-00000006150D.0B2-I can wait until you're done with it.mp3

lines.speaker: Wrecking Ball
lines.filename: 4-Wrecking Ball-000000062624.0B2-(hamster noises) It was shredded for bedding.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000626AB.0B2-I learn so much from observing you.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-0000000617F2.0B2-Aw, likewise! Wait, in a good way, right_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-0000000626AC.0B2-Right_.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 4-Tracer-0000000617F4.0B2-Are you copying me_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000626AF.0B2-I've heard much of your creator. What is she like_.mp3

lines.speaker: Orisa
lines.filename: 2-Orisa-0000000625BD.0B2-Efi's belief in me is humbling. She inspires me to improve each day.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-0000000626B0.0B2-I am... very pleased to hear that.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-00000006380C.0B2-Dr. Liao was not fond of you.mp3

lines.speaker: Moira
lines.filename: 2-Moira-0000000633DD.0B2-Was she any fonder of you_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-00000006380B.0B2-Of course. I was her life's work.mp3

lines.speaker: Moira
lines.filename: 4-Moira-0000000633DE.0B2-It seemed to me she was far more taken with your predecessor.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000643F1.0B2-I do not understand why you enjoy inflicting pain.mp3

lines.speaker: Reaper
lines.filename: 2-Reaper-000000063852.0B2-I'm an enigma. Deal with it.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000643F0.0B2-When I don't replicate human behaviors, I am misunderstood. Are my algorithms insufficient_.mp3

lines.speaker: Symmetra
lines.filename: 2-Symmetra-0000000647D9.0B2-You operate on a level inaccessible to others. I do not see that as a weakness.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-0000000662FF.0B2-You are an R-7000 unit. The ones humans call, um.mp3

lines.speaker: Ramattra
lines.filename: 2-Ramattra-000000063FF3.0B2-Ravagers, yes. _Squad killers._ And... ruder things.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-0000000662FC.0B2-Does it trouble you, being so feared and hated_.mp3

lines.speaker: Ramattra
lines.filename: 4-Ramattra-000000063FF5.0B2-Once. Now, it gives me a warm little feeling inside.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-000000068C53.0B2-Can you tell me what you remember of your Awakening_.mp3

lines.speaker: Ramattra
lines.filename: 2-Ramattra-000000068C75.0B2-It came to me in New York, on a battlefield. I barely survived.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 3-Zenyatta-000000068E9E.0B2-The rise of an emotion. I'd never had one before.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-000000067177.0B2-I have questions about Inti fighting styles.mp3

lines.speaker: Illari
lines.filename: 2-Illari-000000066F9D.0B2-I'm... not qualified to answer them.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-000000067176.0B2-The records show you're a prodigy. Perhaps you're not giving yourself enough credit_.mp3

lines.speaker: Illari
lines.filename: 4-Illari-000000066F97.0B2-Keep reading those records. You'll see how much credit I deserve.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-00000006848A.0B2-I understand you study omnic archaeology.mp3

lines.speaker: Venture
lines.filename: 2-Venture-000000067F0E.0B2-It's only my favorite specialization!.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-00000006848B.0B2-What do you know of the Awakening_ Could Aurora's sentience be replicated_.mp3

lines.speaker: Venture
lines.filename: 4-Venture-000000068088.0B2-That one might be beyond my expertise.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-000000068488.0B2-... and unlike with base 10, you begin at the rightmost number and work left.mp3

lines.speaker: Venture
lines.filename: 2-Venture-000000067F20.0B2-Right. But when did you pick your pronouns_ Did you… download those_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-000000068486.0B2-Do you believe we are discussing “non-binary”, rather than the binary counting system_.mp3

lines.speaker: Venture
lines.filename: 4-Venture-000000067F24.0B2-Oh! Uh... yeah.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-000000068C52.0B2-How are you adjusting to Earth_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 2-Echo-000000068C54.0B2-Another's experiences are not the same as your own. In time, you will form your own conclusions.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-000000068C50.0B2-Yes. Dr. Liao had fond memories of her time attending university there.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 1-Echo-00000006949C.0B2-Overwatch is back. Why not return to search and rescue_.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 2-Freja-000000069559.0B2-Who says I want to go back_.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-00000006949A.0B2-But helping people was your purpose. You were among the best.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 4-Freja-00000006955D.0B2-People change. I wouldn't expect a bot to understand.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 1-Freja-0000000696E8.0B2-A man like you could do well in my line of work.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-000000069B75.0B2-There is no honor in selling one's skills to the highest bidder.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 3-Freja-0000000696E7.0B2-Then I’ll chase bounties while you chase honor. We’ll see who prospers.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 1-Freja-0000000696E2.0B2-I was surprised to learn you're a wanted man. Guess we both let the world down.mp3

lines.speaker: Soldier_ 76
lines.filename: 2-Soldier_ 76-000000069923.0B2-I'm still bringing the world to justice.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 3-Freja-000000069A28.0B2-If that's what you need to tell yourself, Commander.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 1-Freja-0000000696E1.0B2-Strange place, this one. Saw a bounty out for a gang of kids.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 2-Kiriko-000000069B4C.0B2-You didn't take it, right_.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 3-Freja-0000000696E3.0B2-I'd stay on my good side, just in case.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 1-Freja-000000069DCF.0B2-I shouldn't be surprised you joined Talon. You always were good at causing problems.mp3

lines.speaker: Reaper
lines.filename: 2-Reaper-000000069DB3.0B2-(chuckle) You sound just like Sarioglu. Always spouting that righteous garbage.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 3-Freja-000000069DCA.0B2-He stood for something when none of you would.mp3

lines.speaker: Reaper
lines.filename: 4-Reaper-000000069DB4.0B2-Right. And then he walked.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000004BD01.0B2-Why do you ask_.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-00000004A534.0B2-With the way this mission's going, might be my future.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000001FEF9.0B2-Does the suffering of the omnics here trouble you, master_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-000000021FF2.0B2-It does. My brother, Mondatta, gave much to improve their lives, but it was not to be.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000002A7D0.0B2-What would our father think of what we've become, brother_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-00000002F294.0B2-It's hard to say who he'd be more disappointed by.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000002A7C5.0B2-What is it like to have the chance to change the past_.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-00000003714B.0B2-Sometimes it doesn't want to change.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000002A7BF.0B2-Any chocolates today, brother_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-00000002F293.0B2-Those were your amusements, not mine.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000003630C.0B2-Orisa, you grow stronger each time I see you.mp3

lines.speaker: Orisa
lines.filename: 2-Orisa-000000038FE2.0B2-My artificial intelligence makes it possible to learn from my experiences and from everything I observe.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000003630D.0B2-How can I convince you that I am still a man_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 2-Zarya-000000035FC2.0B2-I know what you are. I am only sorry that you do not.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000002A7BE.0B2-Angela, I have some chocolates for you. Not Swiss.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 2-Mercy-00000002A89D.0B2-(mock sigh) I suppose it will have to do. Thank you, Genji.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000002A7D1.0B2-I always liked working with you, Winston. No awkward small talk.mp3

lines.speaker: Winston
lines.filename: 2-Winston-00000002ED96.0B2-Always liked working with you, too. You have... a... great sense of humor.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000000BB09.0B2-So this is what has become of you... a pity.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-000000021194.0B2-I will not be judged by you.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000000BA51.0B2-It is not too late to change your course, brother.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-00000000B1E0.0B2-You are mistaken, brother. I am beyond redemption.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 3-Hanzo-000000021193.0B2-You may call yourself my brother, but you are not the Genji I knew.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550EB.0B2-Are all the warriors of your land women_.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-00000005503B.0B2-Only the best ones.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550EA.0B2-What is stronger, the hammer or the sword_.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-00000005503A.0B2-The hammer is more than just a weapon.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000003630B.0B2-Doomfist, you are truly a worthy foe.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 2-Doomfist-000000041295.0B2-If we fight again, I can't promise you'll walk away this time.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 3-Genji-000000043B11.0B2-Nor can I.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000004BCE2.0B2-This reminds me of our time on base in Switzerland.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 2-Mercy-000000043A71.0B2-You were the only other person who stayed up so late. I enjoyed our conversations.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000003630A.0B2-Angela, what did you wish for on your tanzaku_.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 2-Mercy-000000038084.0B2-If I tell you... does it mean it won't come true_.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000002A7BD.0B2-Do not blame yourself for Mondatta's death. It was not your fault.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-00000003714A.0B2-You don't understand, Genji... I could have saved him. Maybe the world would of been better off if it ha.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550E7.0B2-Do you have an idea about how to break your curse_.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-0000000550C4.0B2-Perhaps I will be freed after my task is completed.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550EC.0B2-When this is done, we should fight together again.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-0000000550D4.0B2-There are still many enemies roaming the world!.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550E5.0B2-What happens when you run out of bullets_.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-000000054FE0.0B2-Nothing good, I reckon.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550DE.0B2-It is strange to see you taking part in the battle, master.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-00000005558E.0B2-There are times even I cannot stand by.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550DD.0B2-Watch yourself, master. I cannot mind your back at all times.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-00000005558D.0B2-Do you think me so helpless_.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 3-Genji-0000000550DC.0B2-Battle is not your way.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550E4.0B2-You move as well as any swordsman I know.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-00000005B80D.0B2-What an insulting comparison.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550DB.0B2-I may need your help to repair my sword and armor when the battle is done.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-000000055552.0B2-Survive the night, and I'll do so gladly.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550D8.0B2-Why do you hunt dragons_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-000000055584.0B2-Because I could not protect my village against a dragon attack. I must atone for my failure.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550E2.0B2-She is no true dragon but surely the summoner is one of your enemies_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-000000055585.0B2-Anyone who would willingly embrace the dragon's fire is an abomination.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000550E1.0B2-Does it bother you that I can summon a dragon_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-00000005556C.0B2-Not tonight.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000005855C.0B2-Thanks for helping me out earlier, Angela.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 2-Mercy-000000058571.0B2-I do seem to be making a habit of saving you. It's a good thing I like you.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 3-Mercy-00000005866C.0B2-Buy me dinner when this is over.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 4-Genji-00000005862F.0B2-It would be my pleasure.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000058631.0B2-The ocean is so beautiful. It reminds me of home.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 2-Mercy-000000058674.0B2-Shame we’re not here to sightsee.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 3-Sojourn-000000058763.0B2-You can take some photos afterwards.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000005861C.0B2-I am grateful for our conversations, Angela. I hope we may resume them when we return to base.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 2-Mercy-00000005865D.0B2-Of course. Assuming you don't find all my research talk too dry.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 3-Genji-00000005861D.0B2-I find it strangely reassuring. Perhaps because you saved my life.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 4-Mercy-00000005865E.0B2-The lengths I go to to find someone willing to talk to me.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000005861E.0B2-I'll be watching your back, Angela. (chuckles) Not that you really need me.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 2-Mercy-00000005865F.0B2-I always feel safer knowing you're there, Genji.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000058629.0B2-I know what it is to leave behind a past you are not proud of.mp3

lines.speaker: Baptiste
lines.filename: 2-Baptiste-00000005B903.0B2-So let's focus on the future, hmm_.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-00000005D9EA.0B2-My cybernetic form came at great cost. But you asked to change_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 2-Sojourn-00000005D9E8.0B2-I learned too young that my body couldn’t always keep up with me. Besides... it’s hard to turn down roc.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000621F3.0B2-You haven't slept.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-000000062252.0B2-(laughs) Yeah. Was up last night, thinking about who we used to be.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 3-Genji-0000000621F4.0B2-I try to focus on the good times.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 4-Cassidy-000000062253.0B2-Hey, yeah. We did have some of those.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000621F8.0B2-My sword and your hammer will lead us to victory.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-000000061140.0B2-If you can't cut them, nail them.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-0000000648D2.0B2-You are as dangerous as your storm!.mp3

lines.speaker: Mei
lines.filename: 2-Mei-00000006462F.0B2-That's nice of you to say! I think.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000063C15.0B2-Master, how do you maintain your tranquility amid endless battles_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-0000000635DB.0B2-I focus on my breathing.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 3-Genji-000000063C19.0B2-But… you don’t breathe.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 4-Zenyatta-0000000635E2.0B2-Indeed.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000063C13.0B2-You have an admirable peace about you.mp3

lines.speaker: Orisa
lines.filename: 2-Orisa-000000062F53.0B2-Things are simple when you protect the innocent.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 3-Genji-000000063C14.0B2-And when you meet the… less-than-innocent_.mp3

lines.speaker: Orisa
lines.filename: 4-Orisa-000000062F54.0B2-Oh! They get the javelin.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000063046.0B2-I live, brother. Why are you still grieving_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-0000000630DE.0B2-You were not the only thing I lost.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000063002.0B2-I still feel that final blow from yesterday's training.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-000000064458.0B2-Aw come on, I didn't hit you that hard.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 3-Genji-00000006301C.0B2-If that is the case, our enemies have much to fear.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000063C20.0B2-You cared too much about how the family perceived you.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-0000000630B0.0B2-Have you ever been the eldest son_.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000063C22.0B2-It was not easy, living in your shadow.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-0000000630DA.0B2-I would have preferred you at my side.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000063C1B.0B2-Talon. You are lucky I do not cut you down where you stand.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 2-Doomfist-0000000644C7.0B2-(laugh) We would welcome the challenge.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000065ADF.0B2-There—the command ship is overhead.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-000000065AE3.0B2-Eyes up! That's our command ship.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 3-Echo-000000065AE1.0B2-There's the Null Sector command ship overhead!.mp3

lines.speaker: Mei
lines.filename: 4-Mei-000000065AE0.0B2-Up there! I see the command ship!.mp3

lines.speaker: Winston
lines.filename: 5-Winston-000000065ADE.0B2-Null Sector has never staged an invasion of this caliber before.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 6-Reinhardt-000000065AE2.0B2-Null Sector has never staged an invasion of this magnitude before!.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 7-Lúcio-00000006575A.0B2-Let's get onboard that ship and shut it down.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000066638.0B2-Ugh. All this sand is getting in my joints.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 2-Echo-000000066639.0B2-I brought compressed air on the dropship for just this occasion!.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000069441.0B2-Angela, have you tried the coffee here_.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 2-Mercy-00000006847C.0B2-Not yet, unfortunately.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 3-Genji-000000069440.0B2-It tastes a bit like yours. Although, it's 'dark roast', not 'charred'.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 4-Mercy-000000068480.0B2-For your information, I LIKE my coffee burnt.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 1-Genji-000000069442.0B2-It is strange to be here again.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 2-Mercy-000000068463.0B2-It's... different. Certainly not the Gibraltar I remember.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 3-Genji-000000069445.0B2-If you are missing old times, I could try almost dying again.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 4-Mercy-000000068462.0B2-(laughs) You make my job hard enough when you're not trying.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000002F2CE.0B2-You say you do science… The good Dr. Junkenstein would profess the same.mp3

lines.speaker: Ana
lines.filename: 2-Ana-00000002EDF9.0B2-Science is a tool and a method. The hand that wields it decides its course.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000002F2DD.0B2-My people would call you a ronin_ a masterless samurai.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-00000002ECF5.0B2-Ronin... I like the sound of that.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000002F2D0.0B2-What difference is there between the witch's magic and your alchemy_.mp3

lines.speaker: Ana
lines.filename: 2-Ana-00000002EDF0.0B2-Alchemy is a science. Her magic is something darker.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000002F2DB.0B2-I sense that you and the soldier have history together.mp3

lines.speaker: Ana
lines.filename: 2-Ana-00000002EDF1.0B2-Indeed. And much of it unhappy.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000000B214.0B2-Think you can do better than me_.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-00000000BA4C.0B2-(scoffs) I am certain of it.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-000000021192.0B2-Where did you hide your treasure_ You could hardly have it on your person.mp3

lines.speaker: Junkrat
lines.filename: 2-Junkrat-00000000B7CF.0B2-Treasure_ Uh... sure I don't know anything you're talking about.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000002117B.0B2-You will never amount to anything.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-00000000BA08.0B2-We shall see, brother.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000000B1FC.0B2-We could have built an empire together.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-00000000BAC9.0B2-That was your dream, not mine.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000000B22C.0B2-I would take my bow against your rifle any day.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-00000000B3A8.0B2-That would be the last mistake you ever made.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000003605B.0B2-Why did you abandon the assassin's art_.mp3

lines.speaker: Ana
lines.filename: 2-Ana-000000038495.0B2-I never was an assassin. I killed only because it was necessary.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-0000000441D6.0B2-I do not fear death.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-00000004BCE5.0B2-No. You find living the challenge.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000005E42D.0B2-I have heard of your experiments. There is no honor in what you do.mp3

lines.speaker: Moira
lines.filename: 2-Moira-000000060438.0B2-Shimada, where do I know that name from_ Oh, that's right... the family of criminals.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-00000005E9C3.0B2-You should focus on training. You waste your time playing games.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 2-D.Va-00000005E9C4.0B2-Why don't you give them a try_ Maybe then you'd frown less!.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 3-Hanzo-00000005E9C5.0B2-I... (scoffs)!.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-000000061F8A.0B2-Perhaps today, the dragon will be sated.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-000000062606.0B2-That was so artistic! Are you a poet too_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 3-Hanzo-000000061F8B.0B2-I was, once. Now I seek peace in other ways.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 4-Brigitte-00000006260E.0B2-Still sounds pretty poetic to me.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-0000000630AD.0B2-I have always been bound to my duty. Now, I have nothing.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-000000063C1F.0B2-There is always a way to make something from nothing, brother.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-0000000630B7.0B2-Each day, I grow stronger. Yet the man in the mirror never appears to change.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-0000000635FB.0B2-A mirror reflects only what can be seen.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 3-Hanzo-0000000630B9.0B2-Your platitudes will not work on me the way they did my brother.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 4-Zenyatta-0000000635FA.0B2-And yet, you sound just like he did.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-0000000630BA.0B2-What are you wearing_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo

lines.speaker: Hanzo

lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-000000067466.0B2-Is Murphy a lot to handle_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 3-Hanzo-000000067465.0B2-Maybe one day. When I settle down.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-000000067462.0B2-Keep frowning, and you'll end up looking like me.mp3

lines.filename: 2-Illari-000000066AE5.0B2-You mean you weren't born like that_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 3-Hanzo-000000067464.0B2-I was not. Were you_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo

lines.filename: 1-Hanzo-000000069B6D.0B2-Have you heard from your father_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo

lines.speaker: Hanzo

lines.speaker: Wuyang

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 3-Hanzo-000000069B72.0B2-He wasted his time fooling around instead of learning responsibility.mp3

lines.speaker: Wuyang

lines.filename: 6-Hazard-000000067BD3.0B2-Right, well... looks class!.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 1-Hazard-000000067C41.0B2-You know, I really used to idolize you.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 3-Hazard-0000000682EC.0B2-What makes you think I'm lookin' for a cure_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 1-Hazard-0000000684E1.0B2-_Pain makes power._ You really believe that_.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 2-Doomfist-0000000686E5.0B2-You adapted after great injury. Is that not strength through suffering_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 3-Hazard-00000006844D.0B2-Nah. It's my friends that made me who I am, I've them to thank.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 4-Doomfist-0000000686E6.0B2-And more to lose than you think.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 1-Hazard-0000000682EF.0B2-You know, if you really wanted to commit to the whole spider bit, you'd get some extra legs.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker

lines.speaker: Hazard

lines.filename: 1-Hazard-00000006844E.0B2-How much did that skin mod cost you_.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-000000068526.0B2-More than you'd be willing to pay.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 1-Hazard-000000068451.0B2-What a getup. Do you believe in fairytales as well_.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-0000000686EA.0B2-Of course! A little fantasy never hurt anyone.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 3-Hazard-000000068450.0B2-Oh I beg to differ. Lot of dark tales where I'm from.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 1-Hazard-0000000684E6.0B2-Awrite there, friend_.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 3-Hazard-0000000684E4.0B2-Nah, I'll just take a good hit to the noggin. Does the same thing!.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 3-Hazard-000000068452.0B2-Ah. Bit o' both, then.mp3

lines.filename: 1-Hazard-000000069302.0B2-Look what's happened to Overwatch's golden boy! I liked you better dead.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 3-Hazard-000000069310.0B2-Crawled out of it, actually. Your lot didn't dig it quite deep enough.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe

lines.speaker: Juno
lines.filename: 3-Juno-000000068A27.0B2-Intriguing! But... I do not feel particularly mighty.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt

lines.speaker: Juno
lines.filename: 1-Juno-000000068A21.0B2-If you are a knight... should I call you Sir Wilhelm_.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt

lines.filename: 1-Juno-000000068E62.0B2-Does your turret have a name_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn

lines.speaker: Juno
lines.filename: 3-Juno-000000068E5E.0B2-But you are always calling it your baby. I thought all babies had names.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn

lines.speaker: Juno
lines.filename: 3-Juno-000000068E5C.0B2-(embarrassed laugh) I suppose it must have been a spectacle.mp3

lines.filename: 1-Juno-000000069AC5.0B2-A bounty hunter! Are you here to detain me_.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja

lines.speaker: Juno
lines.filename: 3-Juno-000000069AC7.0B2-Ah, I am relieved! But also slightly disheartened.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer

lines.speaker: Winston
lines.filename: 5-Winston-0000000620C5.0B2-(chuckle) Is that true_.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte

lines.filename: 9-Reinhardt-0000000605B8.0B2-What_ Haha!.mp3

lines.filename: 11-Kiriko-00000005EF86.0B2-Once was enough.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-00000005EFE8.0B2-Mm. I'll tell her you're thinking about picking it back up.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-00000005EF65.0B2-So, how'd you pull all those heists_.mp3

lines.speaker: Junkrat
lines.filename: 2-Junkrat-00000005EF61.0B2-Bombs!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-00000005EF47.0B2-Uh huh. And_.mp3

lines.speaker: Junkrat
lines.filename: 4-Junkrat-00000005EF64.0B2-Was—was there supposed to be another step_.mp3

lines.speaker: Junkrat
lines.filename: 5-Junkrat-00000005EF56.0B2-Get this_ More bombs!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-00000005EF85.0B2-You look familiar. Are you the loud one_.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-000000062088.0B2-No, I am Reinhardt Wilhelm! The one with the hammer and shield!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-00000005EF8A.0B2-But not the loud one. Sure.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000062785.0B2-I like your mask.mp3

lines.speaker: Roadhog
lines.filename: 2-Roadhog-0000000621FF.0B2-(grunts).mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000062786.0B2-I said, I like your mask, dude.mp3

lines.speaker: Roadhog
lines.filename: 4-Roadhog-000000062200.0B2-Okay.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-00000005EF8B.0B2-Listened to your album the other day.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 2-Lúcio-000000061D8C.0B2-Oh, uh, did you like it_.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-00000005EFDE.0B2-Not sure there was enough bass. I could almost hear the other sounds.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 4-Lúcio-000000061D98.0B2-Ha! I’ll crank it up next time!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-00000005EFE2.0B2-You check out the new Antler Antler album_.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 2-Lúcio-000000061D8D.0B2-You've heard of them_.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-00000005EFDC.0B2-Yeah. So... what'd you think_.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 4-Lúcio-000000061D97.0B2-Nobody uses fifteen electric guitars like those guys!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-00000006932B.0B2-(sigh) They discontinued my favorite moisturizer. Got any recommendations_.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 2-D.Va-00000006239B.0B2-Eh. Sorry, I don't use creams. I just splash some water on my face and call it a day.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000069311.0B2-What_ At least use sunscreen!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000063813.0B2-(Japanese)_ Yikes... You look cheery.mp3

lines.speaker: Moira
lines.filename: 2-Moira-0000000633E2.0B2-As cheery as you are significant.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000062DB3.0B2-Hey, you're pretty cool.mp3

lines.speaker: Orisa
lines.filename: 2-Orisa-0000000637FA.0B2-Yes, and you are a perfect 37 degrees Celsius.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000062DB5.0B2-You got me there.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000062DBF.0B2-You have a bandage_.mp3

lines.speaker: Moira
lines.filename: 2-Moira-00000006441D.0B2-Who exactly do you think I am_.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000062DC1.0B2-Someone who carries bandages_ Guess not.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-0000000642A2.0B2-_Swift as the wind_, huh, Genji_.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-0000000648D1.0B2-Even swifter, thanks to you.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000064474.0B2-Are we... dreaming_.mp3

lines.speaker: Junker Queen
lines.filename: 2-Junker Queen-000000064475.0B2-Feels more like a bloody nightmare!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-0000000646A8.0B2-You're a sleuth, huh_ What case are you on_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 2-Sojourn-0000000646A7.0B2-Right now_ _The Case of What The Hell's Going On In This Town._.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-0000000648D9.0B2-I'd try a shorter title.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-0000000646AE.0B2-You've been through Adlersbrunn before, right_.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe
lines.filename: 2-Ashe-0000000646AF.0B2-Once or twice.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-0000000646B1.0B2-Ever cross paths with a swordmaster_.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 4-Kiriko-0000000646B0.0B2-Ever cross paths with an archer_.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe
lines.filename: 5-Ashe-0000000646B2.0B2-I steer clear of trouble like him.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-0000000646C2.0B2-The Summoner_ She was... dead, wasn't she_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 2-Sojourn-000000064BEB.0B2-Seems the Bride stoked her back to life.mp3

lines.speaker: Junker Queen
lines.filename: 3-Junker Queen-0000000646C1.0B2-Well she's dead again now. And the Bride's next, once we bust through this door!.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe
lines.filename: 4-Ashe-000000064BD8.0B2-Step aside, gals. My dynamite will burn this door to the ground.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-0000000646EC.0B2-You never mentioned the castle is haunted.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe
lines.filename: 2-Ashe-0000000646ED.0B2-Ever seen one that wasn't_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 3-Sojourn-0000000646EB.0B2-Stay focused. That ghost could be back any minute.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-00000006475C.0B2-Did the Bride reanimate all these zomnics_.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe
lines.filename: 2-Ashe-0000000648AC.0B2-Seems Junkenstein wasn't the only _inventive_ one.mp3

lines.speaker: Junker Queen
lines.filename: 3-Junker Queen-000000064A7A.0B2-Question. Is she married to the doctor_ Or his monster_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 4-Sojourn-000000064A75.0B2-Really not important right now.mp3

lines.speaker: Junker Queen
lines.filename: 5-Junker Queen-000000064A6E.0B2-(scoff) Says you.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000064A51.0B2-I can feel the Bride's aura. She's still close.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 2-Sojourn-000000064A53.0B2-We can't let her flip any more switches.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 3-Sojourn-000000064A72.0B2-Think you can predict the one she'll pick next_.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 4-Kiriko-000000064A50.0B2-I see her... choosing the one we least expect.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 5-Sojourn-000000064A73.0B2-This is why people hate fortune tellers.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000064A98.0B2-Glad to see other survivors!.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 2-Sojourn-000000064A97.0B2-We won't last long out here. Let's get inside and figure this out.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000065B76.0B2-Hammer man. Any German music you recommend_.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-000000065623.0B2-Krankenwagen Grün. (laughs) The best band of the 2030s!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000065B7A.0B2-Never heard of them.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 4-Reinhardt-000000065624.0B2-What_ They defined techno-polka. You young people have no culture at all!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000065B77.0B2-Might be tricky keeping this bunch alive.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 2-Lifeweaver-000000065906.0B2-Between the two of us_ How can we fail_.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000065B78.0B2-What if they run off without us_.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 4-Lifeweaver-000000065905.0B2-Don't worry. I have a plan for that.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000069319.0B2-I like your nickname. How'd you get it_.mp3

lines.speaker: Venture
lines.filename: 2-Venture-000000067239.0B2-I gave it to myself!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000069316.0B2-Isn't that a little... tacky_.mp3

lines.speaker: Venture
lines.filename: 4-Venture-00000006723A.0B2-Oh, very!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000069320.0B2-You look nervous. Want to meditate_.mp3

lines.speaker: Juno
lines.filename: 2-Juno-000000068A22.0B2-I am interested, but it sounds difficult.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000069324.0B2-I'll try to walk you through it. Take a deep breath, and try to calm your thoughts.mp3

lines.speaker: Juno
lines.filename: 4-Juno-000000068A23.0B2-Alright. (sigh) ...I am incompatible with this activity.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-00000006932D.0B2-The Hashimoto run hourly patrols. We can sneak into the castle when they change shifts.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-000000069B6F.0B2-I am... impressed. Your preparations are quite diligent.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000069313.0B2-Well, I had to kill time until someone came back.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 4-Hanzo-000000069B71.0B2-Right. Then I will make your patience worthwhile.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000069325.0B2-You should come home, Genji. We need your help.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-000000069452.0B2-There are others in the world who need saving.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000069326.0B2-When I was a kid, you said you'd always be there for me.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 4-Genji-00000006944F.0B2-You're old enough to know it's not that simple.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-00000006931D.0B2-Think I can use your ring tech on my bike_ I have a race coming up soon.mp3

lines.speaker: Juno
lines.filename: 2-Juno-000000068E7B.0B2-Would that be considered cheating_.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-00000006931B.0B2-No! Well... maybe.mp3

lines.speaker: Juno
lines.filename: 4-Juno-000000068E69.0B2-(gasp) How thrilling! We will make it happen!.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 1-Kiriko-000000069B49.0B2-I have some bounties you might want. Five of them, actually.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 2-Freja-00000006986F.0B2-(chuckle) I'm good at what I do, kid, but even I'm not going to mess with the Hashimoto.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 3-Kiriko-000000069B4A.0B2-All right... Then how are you with rescue missions_.mp3

lines.speaker: Freja
lines.filename: 4-Freja-00000006986E.0B2-Ah. If you've got the money, let's talk.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-000000064570.0B2-Have I seen you around the arcology_.mp3

lines.speaker: Orisa
lines.filename: 2-Orisa-000000067C28.0B2-My creator, Efi, spoke at a conference there.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-0000000645BE.0B2-Ah, yes! I didn't know what was more impressive_ her presentation on ferrofluid injectors, or her ap.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-0000000645A6.0B2-Satya, remember our good old days at the academy_.mp3

lines.speaker: Symmetra
lines.filename: 2-Symmetra-000000065E32.0B2-You complained constantly about everything, and then you dropped out.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-0000000645A9.0B2-I saw it as an... early graduation.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-0000000658AA.0B2-I heard you hosted my dearest Satya in Suravasa.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-0000000658E2.0B2-She is a delight. How do you know her_.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-0000000658AB.0B2-We were roommates at the academy. My, did she hate it when I left dishes in the sink.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-000000066395.0B2-What is your fascination with artificial decay_.mp3

lines.speaker: Moira
lines.filename: 2-Moira-000000067705.0B2-To reverse entropy, we must tame it.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-000000066393.0B2-But inflicting it on yourself_ You're withering away!.mp3

lines.speaker: Moira
lines.filename: 4-Moira-000000067706.0B2-I've always thrived under a deadline.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-000000066396.0B2-You're so old-fashioned, Reinhardt. A hammer_ How marvelous!.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-000000065DEF.0B2-I suppose you think I should have a giant laser gun.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-000000066394.0B2-No, lean into it! Get Lindholm to build you one of his big robotic horses.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 4-Cassidy-00000006683A.0B2-What did you just say_.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-0000000661BA.0B2-I've got reservations at a fantastic restaurant, but I'm not too sure who to invite.mp3

lines.speaker: Baptiste
lines.filename: 2-Baptiste-000000065E23.0B2-I know a guy.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-00000006627B.0B2-Is he by any chance a dashing ex-mercenary from the Caribbean_.mp3

lines.speaker: Baptiste
lines.filename: 4-Baptiste-000000065E26.0B2-(chuckling) He might just be!.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-000000066391.0B2-What do you miss most about the academy, Satya_.mp3

lines.speaker: Symmetra
lines.filename: 2-Symmetra-000000065E34.0B2-Your snoring. It helped me sleep.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-000000066388.0B2-How on earth are you even larger than I thought you'd be_.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-000000065DEE.0B2-That's simple! You see, I am standing very close to you.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-00000006637C.0B2-And I'd like it to remain that way!.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-000000066383.0B2-Are you and Roadhog together_.mp3

lines.speaker: Junkrat
lines.filename: 2-Junkrat-000000065EF6.0B2-Do you ever see us apart_.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-000000066389.0B2-No, I mean are you a couple_.mp3

lines.speaker: Junkrat
lines.filename: 4-Junkrat-000000065EF7.0B2-Yes, a couple of dashing rogues! Not sure what you're missing here.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-00000006638B.0B2-I need durable volunteers for some kinetic biolight experiments. Can I count on you_.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 2-Sojourn-00000006610D.0B2-I'm not your best subject. This body isn't exactly cutting-edge tech anymore.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-00000006638C.0B2-Ms. Chase, I insist that you never tear yourself down in my presence again.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn
lines.filename: 4-Sojourn-00000006610E.0B2-(chuckling) All right, I get the picture.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-000000066229.0B2-It's monstrous that you were kept locked up for so long.mp3

lines.speaker: Echo
lines.filename: 2-Echo-000000066304.0B2-It didn't feel very long to me.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-0000000661BD.0B2-Well, should your jailers ever come knocking again, I know a place you'd be safe.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-000000066385.0B2-I love the warmth in your music. Your newest album is like listening to a sunrise.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 2-Lúcio-000000066819.0B2-Wow, thanks. You should tell that to my critics.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-00000006637D.0B2-Critics_ You_ No! I won't stand for it.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 1-Lifeweaver-0000000661B6.0B2-I envy your amicable relationship with your family.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-000000066831.0B2-You aren't in touch with yours_.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
lines.filename: 3-Lifeweaver-0000000661B7.0B2-We had a shouting match not long ago, if that counts.mp3

lines.speaker: Lifeweaver
