lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000037EE4.0B2-Fareeha, any plans for the winter_.mp3

lines.speaker: Pharah
lines.filename: 2-Pharah-000000036AF9.0B2-I'm flying home to see my dad.mp3

lines.speaker: Pharah
lines.filename: 3-Pharah-00000004CE0D.0B2-I'm going to head to Canada to see my dad.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000055415.0B2-I hate working with these talking tin cans.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-00000000AD51.0B2-Your will is strong, my friend. But in time, I know you will realize we are not so different.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005557C.0B2-It is hard to trust that which I cannot see with my own eyes.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-0000000550CF.0B2-I'd shake your hand but we are a little busy now.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005557D.0B2-Are you a magic spirit_.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-0000000550CE.0B2-Just another cursed traveler.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000055551.0B2-I find your religion unnerving, monk.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-00000005558F.0B2-My beliefs are simply in the fundamental ways of life and nature, nothing more.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000055581.0B2-The single mindedness of Dr. Junkenstein's creations reminds me of your own.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-0000000555A0.0B2-You wound me.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000055582.0B2-Is that even possible_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000055583.0B2-Who were you before you entered the monastery_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-00000005559F.0B2-No one of note. Just one of thousands like me.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 3-Zenyatta-000000055590.0B2-But one moment of clarity changed everything.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000055553.0B2-I hear you're an authority on dragons.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-0000000550DA.0B2-Why do you ask_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000055554.0B2-I hunt them.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 4-Genji-0000000550D9.0B2-Then I believe you heard wrong.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 5-Torbjörn-00000005556B.0B2-Touchy subject.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005B425.0B2-When we rebuilt after the Omnic Crisis, I swore I'd never let Gothenburg be destroyed again.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-00000005B424.0B2-This time we'll stop them, Papa. I promise.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005B845.0B2-Where I'm from, we throw deserters into the sea.mp3

lines.speaker: Baptiste
lines.filename: 2-Baptiste-00000005B8F6.0B2-Well, I'm a pretty good swimmer.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005B84A.0B2-You know what_ You're alright, Renegade.mp3

lines.speaker: Baptiste
lines.filename: 2-Baptiste-00000005B8FB.0B2-For a lizard-obsessed misanthrope, you're pretty agreeable yourself.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-00000005B84B.0B2-Watch it.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005B846.0B2-Vikings are the greatest raiders of wealth and treasure the world has ever seen.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe
lines.filename: 2-Ashe-00000005B9C1.0B2-Vikings never met me.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005B848.0B2-I might be able to make a few improvements to that weapon of yours, Outlaw.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe
lines.filename: 2-Ashe-00000005B9C4.0B2-It's serving me just fine, thanks.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005B852.0B2-I wish we could get that Immortality Field to work on my turret.mp3

lines.speaker: Baptiste
lines.filename: 2-Baptiste-00000005B905.0B2-But then our enemies would have no chance!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005B853.0B2-Baptiste, was it_ How did a mercenary like yourself come by such advanced technologies_.mp3

lines.speaker: Baptiste
lines.filename: 2-Baptiste-00000005B908.0B2-Oh, I just make use of what I find lying around.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005B854.0B2-Such intriguing sonic displacement technology!.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 2-Lúcio-00000005B7FD.0B2-Thanks! My dad invented it. You two would get along great.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005B849.0B2-After we prevail, will you join us for a banquet, Countess_.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-00000005B813.0B2-I prefer to feast in private. Typically with a single guest.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005C00E.0B2-So you're working with Sojourn again, Wilhelm_ How's that going_.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-00000005C00F.0B2-We have our differences... but I am willing to overlook them.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005BCBB.0B2-I hope the old crew's doing well. I haven’t seen some of them in years.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-00000005BCBC.0B2-Lena is as cheery as ever. And Angela hasn’t aged a day.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-00000005BCBD.0B2-I’d expect nothing less.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005F105.0B2-How about you let me build you a new mech_.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 2-D.Va-00000005F12B.0B2-Uh... I don't know... I heard your inventions take five minutes to boot up.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-00000005F104.0B2-That was once!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005EBF5.0B2-This is not how I envisioned retirement.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-00000005EBF6.0B2-Come on, Papa. You don't know how to stop working!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-00000005EBF7.0B2-That's not true. I took your mother to Greece for our anniversary.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 4-Brigitte-00000005EBF8.0B2-Yeah, and fixed a whole subway system while you were there!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000006127F.0B2-(sigh) Just yesterday, Brigitte was a toddler making trouble.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-000000061287.0B2-Papa! Not right now!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000060F08.0B2-Brigitte, did you check if you brought enough repair packs for everyone_.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-0000000625DF.0B2-Of course Papa. I'm not a little girl anymore.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000060F0A.0B2-You'll always be my little girl.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 4-Brigitte-0000000625E0.0B2-You're embarrassing me.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000060F0C.0B2-Are you ever going to tell me Valkryie's airfoil ratio_.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 2-Mercy-000000061FA8.0B2-Are you going to tell me Ingrid's apple pie recipe_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000060F0E.0B2-Hmph, you drive a hard bargain.mp3

lines.speaker: Mercy
lines.filename: 4-Mercy-000000061FA9.0B2-I'll just ask her myself.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000060F10.0B2-Remind me to install a firewall system in you. Can't be too careful nowadays.mp3

lines.speaker: Bastion
lines.filename: 2-Bastion-000000062C12.0B2-(happy beeps).mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000060F12.0B2-For the last time, tell Ganymede my beard is not a nest!.mp3

lines.speaker: Bastion
lines.filename: 2-Bastion-000000062BFA.0B2-(disappointed beeps).mp3

lines.speaker: Bastion
lines.filename: 3-Bastion-000000062BFE.0B2-(disappointed beeps).mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 4-Torbjörn-000000060F14.0B2-Don't you beep boop me. No is no.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000060F15.0B2-Who developed those orbs of yours_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-0000000621E0.0B2-Ask not who their maker is, but what they mean.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000060F17.0B2-You don't know, do you_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 4-Zenyatta-0000000621E1.0B2-I embrace the unknown.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000060F1F.0B2-Brigitte isn't meddling too much with your armor, is she_.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-0000000616B5.0B2-Somebody's worried he's turning obsolete.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000060F21.0B2-That's parenthood for you.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000006113B.0B2-Retirement looks good on you Ana.mp3

lines.speaker: Ana
lines.filename: 2-Ana-00000006251D.0B2-Aren't we too old for flattery_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-00000006113D.0B2-Hmph, we're still alive and kicking!.mp3

lines.speaker: Ana
lines.filename: 4-Ana-00000006251E.0B2-Still young at heart, I see.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000061141.0B2-Don't you ever want to settle down_.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-00000006225C.0B2-Maybe. Trouble is, I got some itchy feet.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000061143.0B2-I've got some powder for that.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000061149.0B2-(sighs) I guess it takes all kinds to make a world.mp3

lines.speaker: Roadhog
lines.filename: 2-Roadhog-000000062204.0B2-(grunts).mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-0000000611AD.0B2-Don't roll over me, you hear_ I'm not a bowling pin.mp3

lines.speaker: Wrecking Ball
lines.filename: 2-Wrecking Ball-000000062620.0B2-(hamster noises) He is unable to promise zero casualties.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-0000000611AF.0B2-Let me talk to him face-to-face.mp3

lines.speaker: Wrecking Ball
lines.filename: 4-Wrecking Ball-000000062621.0B2-That is not advisable.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-0000000611B1.0B2-If you ever need a punching bag, I got plenty of metal that needs scrapping.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 2-Zarya-000000062360.0B2-That is the greatest present I've ever gotten.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-0000000611B3.0B2-Maybe you need better friends.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000006121F.0B2-I got some new prototypes that need testing. Thought of you.mp3

lines.speaker: Baptiste
lines.filename: 2-Baptiste-00000006271B.0B2-Me_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000061221.0B2-Need someone who knows what they're doing.mp3

lines.speaker: Baptiste
lines.filename: 4-Baptiste-00000006271C.0B2-I'm flattered and honored.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000006207F.0B2-Dr. Zhou! You've made quite the name for yourself.mp3

lines.speaker: Mei
lines.filename: 2-Mei-000000061CC5.0B2-Oh, thank you! I think there's always more to learn.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000062080.0B2-Quit being so humble. Nothing wrong with being proud of your work!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000006122C.0B2-You know Fareeha, it's not a sign of weakness if you take it easy sometimes.mp3

lines.speaker: Pharah
lines.filename: 2-Pharah-0000000620BB.0B2-Mistakes arise when people turn careless.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-00000006122E.0B2-(sighs) Like mother, like daughter.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000062084.0B2-I bet my turret's a better shot than you.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-000000062141.0B2-And what are you willing to bet on_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000062085.0B2-The Lindholm reputation!.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 4-Widowmaker-000000063FDD.0B2-How about your other eye_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000062086.0B2-You sure you won't let me upgrade that arm_.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-00000006227C.0B2-Ah, you know I like it old school.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-0000000616C2.0B2-How's Winston_ Did he ever get that shield generator to stop exploding_.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-00000006260C.0B2-Wh... I... think so_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-0000000616C3.0B2-That's the problem. You never expect something to explode, until it does.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000062087.0B2-I helped them with a few things.mp3

lines.speaker: Junkrat
lines.filename: 2-Junkrat-0000000622FA.0B2-What uh—what sort of things_ Asking for a friend.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000063E7A.0B2-Hey. Someone repaired my turret while I was napping!.mp3

lines.speaker: Wrecking Ball
lines.filename: 2-Wrecking Ball-000000063957.0B2-(hamster noises) He says, _You're welcome._.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-0000000665FD.0B2-I won't let these b'orlaxes get the better of us!.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 2-Doomfist-0000000665FE.0B2-Watch your tongue. The b'orlaxes might hear you!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-0000000665FB.0B2-Meetroo ja paree'nee, du teek-teek-wu'ree!.mp3

lines.speaker: Wrecking Ball
lines.filename: 2-Wrecking Ball-0000000665FC.0B2-(hamster noises) New profanity entry detected. Uploading to database.mp3

lines.speaker: Winston
lines.filename: 3-Winston-0000000668B5.0B2-Gre'vnax am Grel'nor!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-0000000665F2.0B2-How come Dorioux gives you good deals but not me_.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe
lines.filename: 2-Ashe-0000000665F4.0B2-Dunno. Maybe you're just easy to manipulate.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-00000005F0A5.0B2-My new freeze turrets need setting up. Even you're probably smart enough to figure them out.mp3

lines.speaker: Reinhardt
lines.filename: 2-Reinhardt-000000061272.0B2-You sure they work, or do you need to futz with them for half an hour_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000066708.0B2-Hmm, this one does need a bit of work. I'll just repair it with my hammer. Stand by!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-0000000671F8.0B2-Who do I have to bother to get my hands on your pylon's blueprints_.mp3

lines.speaker: Illari
lines.filename: 2-Illari-000000066E39.0B2-I don't know. Those files were destroyed in... an accident.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-0000000671F4.0B2-That's a shame. I'll just reverse engineer it then!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000068ECD.0B2-You Wayfinders seem to like digging up old problems.mp3

lines.speaker: Venture
lines.filename: 2-Venture-000000067F11.0B2-And we couldn't do it without Ironclad tools!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000068EED.0B2-Maybe you should try some Ironclad judgment.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000068ED0.0B2-Last night, I had an awful nightmare. My turret was attached to my head!.mp3

lines.speaker: Hazard
lines.filename: 2-Hazard-000000068FD0.0B2-That's brilliant! I've a friend that could make that happen for ye!.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000068ECF.0B2-Humph. Some dreams ought to stay dreams.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 1-Torbjörn-000000068EF1.0B2-What's the secret behind your flight mechanism_.mp3

lines.speaker: Illari
lines.filename: 2-Illari-000000068C8A.0B2-I don't know the specifics. Something about thermodynamics, I think.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 3-Torbjörn-000000068ECB.0B2-Of course! Convection currents! Why didn't I think of that_.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-00000000AFC3.0B2-Lúcio, I'll race ya!.mp3

lines.speaker: Lúcio
lines.filename: 2-Lúcio-00000000B512.0B2-Oh, you're on!.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-000000021E70.0B2-Aren't you warm wearing all that_.mp3

lines.speaker: Mei
lines.filename: 2-Mei-00000000BBB8.0B2-Yes, but it's too late to change!.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-00000002CDE9.0B2-Don't think I don't recognize that device of yours. I know you stole it.mp3

lines.speaker: Sombra
lines.filename: 2-Sombra-000000030562.0B2-What can I say_ A girl just has to have the latest tech.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-000000021E71.0B2-Wow, it’s an honor to meet a member of the Shambali. Mondatta was an inspiration to me.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-000000021FF4.0B2-To us all. I miss him greatly.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-00000000AFD4.0B2-Whacha lookin' at_.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-00000000B3A7.0B2-An annoyance.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-00000000AFA5.0B2-Oh, Winston... got you your favorite!.mp3

lines.speaker: Winston
lines.filename: 2-Winston-00000000B057.0B2-For the last time_ no more bananas!.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550B4.0B2-How can you trust the countess after she slew your master_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-000000055596.0B2-Did I say I trusted her_.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550D2.0B2-In my former life, I would have gladly fought by your side.mp3

lines.speaker: Brigitte
lines.filename: 2-Brigitte-000000055039.0B2-And I would fight with you in the next.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-00000005509C.0B2-I guess they'll let anyone be a pilot these days.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550D1.0B2-I want a word with you after this fight is over.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-00000005B803.0B2-I don't.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550C2.0B2-I've heard rumors that you've slain a dragon.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-00000005557A.0B2-Never slain, but I will, or I will die in the attempt.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550C3.0B2-How did you learn your craft_.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-00000005557B.0B2-I was one of many apprentices, (chuckles) but rose the highest.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550D5.0B2-Time has greatly changed us both.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-0000000550E9.0B2-We are all of us always changing.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550CD.0B2-I'm happy to fight at your side again.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-0000000550E8.0B2-Let us hope that this time it works out better in the end.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550D3.0B2-Would you tell me more about your religion_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-000000055592.0B2-Our purpose is to show everyone that in the iris, we are all one people.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550CB.0B2-I don't think I've ever seen you sleep.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-000000055595.0B2-Meditation is all I require to sustain myself.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550CA.0B2-What happened to your arm, gunslinger_.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-000000054FD1.0B2-It was claimed by a darker power.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550C9.0B2-You seem like a man haunted by the past.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-000000054FD2.0B2-How can you tell_.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 3-Tracer-0000000550C8.0B2-Haunting's something of a specialty of mine.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550C7.0B2-I'm surprised to see you taking a side in this fight.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-000000054FD3.0B2-I'm going to be well paid.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-0000000550B1.0B2-Getting a little tired_ You seem short of breath.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-000000054FD6.0B2-I'll be fine. I try not to move too much.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 1-Tracer-000000058556.0B2-I've heard Commander Morrison's been under pressure to disband this strike team.mp3

lines.speaker: Winston
lines.filename: 2-Winston-00000005856C.0B2-But we're only just getting started.mp3

lines.speaker: Sojourn

lines.filename: 2-Tracer-0000000550B2.0B2-Are you so sure about that_.mp3

lines.filename: 1-Widowmaker-00000005B802.0B2-When this night is done, I will not return.mp3

lines.filename: 1-Widowmaker-00000005B80E.0B2-We'd best finish this business before the dawn.mp3

lines.filename: 1-Widowmaker-00000005B820.0B2-Brave of you to show your face after what happened in Monte Cristi.mp3

lines.filename: 1-Widowmaker-00000005B81F.0B2-Hello Baptiste. Think you can hide from Talon forever_.mp3

lines.filename: 1-Widowmaker-00000005B80F.0B2-You're that guard who deserted his post. Didn't we pay you enough_.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 1-Widowmaker-00000005B819.0B2-I hope you're not planning to abandon this fight too.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 1-Widowmaker-00000005B812.0B2-When this is over, Renegade, I'll give you one night's head start.mp3

lines.filename: 3-Zarya-000000063C41.0B2-(thoughtful grunt).mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-000000063C42.0B2-Tell me, omnic. Do you dream_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-0000000635E4.0B2-I dream of peace. And, sometimes, falling.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 3-Zarya-000000063C43.0B2-Perhaps we have more in common than I thought.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-000000063C48.0B2-You do too much cardio, not enough weight training.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 2-Kiriko-000000062DB7.0B2-I'll lift some weights if you go jogging with me.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 3-Zarya-000000063C49.0B2-We will see if you can keep up.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-000000063C4A.0B2-So, you throw tiny daggers_.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 2-Kiriko-000000062DC3.0B2-Is that a problem_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 3-Zarya-000000063C4B.0B2-Depends. How often do you miss_.mp3

lines.speaker: Kiriko
lines.filename: 4-Kiriko-000000062DC5.0B2-Let's find out.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-000000063C44.0B2-You rarely preach about victory.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 2-Zenyatta-0000000635EE.0B2-Is victory so important_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 3-Zarya-000000063C45.0B2-If it isn't, why are you here_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 4-Zenyatta-0000000635EF.0B2-Indeed, why are we here_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-0000000648D0.0B2-Your pets are quite handsome.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-000000063CA5.0B2-The dragons are not _pets_… but thank you.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-0000000648CE.0B2-Rat. Say _thank you_.mp3

lines.speaker: Junkrat
lines.filename: 2-Junkrat-000000063D67.0B2-Ah! My most sinciferest thanks to the second most intimidating person I know.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-0000000648CD.0B2-Nowhere to run.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 2-Doomfist-0000000644CF.0B2-Nowhere to hide!.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-0000000648CC.0B2-Good thinking, omnic! Uh... processing. Whatever.mp3

lines.speaker: Bastion
lines.filename: 2-Bastion-00000006440C.0B2-(giggly beeps).mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-0000000648CB.0B2-Just like we planned. I pulled them together, and.mp3

lines.speaker: Pharah
lines.filename: 2-Pharah-00000006401D.0B2-Yeah yeah yeah, I blew them up.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-000000065F5E.0B2-You talk big, but can you deliver_.mp3

lines.speaker: Mauga
lines.filename: 2-Mauga-000000066A3A.0B2-With a big red bow on top.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 3-Zarya-000000065F64.0B2-I prefer pink.mp3

lines.speaker: Mauga
lines.filename: 4-Mauga-000000066A39.0B2-For you, I can make it happen.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 1-Zarya-000000065F5C.0B2-I'm the muscle of the team.mp3

lines.speaker: Mauga
lines.filename: 2-Mauga-000000066A37.0B2-No, I'm the muscle!.mp3

lines.speaker: Zarya
lines.filename: 3-Zarya-000000065F63.0B2-Well, you are certainly not the brains.mp3

lines.speaker: Mauga
lines.filename: 4-Mauga-000000066A24.0B2-(chuckles) I like you.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-00000000AD3B.0B2-So this is where you grew up. You must show me around!.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-00000000BA28.0B2-That was another life.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-000000044269.0B2-Symmetra, you speak of law and of order, but you must know that life is chaotic by its very nature.mp3

lines.speaker: Symmetra
lines.filename: 2-Symmetra-000000043E9C.0B2-To be lectured about chaos and disorder from a machine.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-000000021FF1.0B2-I sense within you the same rage that once consumed your brother.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-000000021196.0B2-We are nothing alike.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-000000044268.0B2-Genji, how was your reunion with your brother_.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-00000004BCE4.0B2-He is still not ready for time to flow forward again.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 3-Zenyatta-00000004C50F.0B2-Time is a river. It may be stopped for a while, but it will always flow the same direction.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-00000004C50E.0B2-I believe that you could find peace, if you were to search within yourself.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 2-Doomfist-000000041465.0B2-What is tranquility but stagnation_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-00000002EFC4.0B2-Do you have any dreams, my friend_.mp3

lines.speaker: Orisa
lines.filename: 2-Orisa-0000000352AB.0B2-I do not dream as humans do... but it is my desire to become the hero Efi believes that I am.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-00000000AD55.0B2-It is good to fight alongside one of my brightest pupils.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-00000000BA50.0B2-And you, master.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-00000000AD2E.0B2-Tell me your thoughts, my friend.mp3

lines.speaker: Bastion
lines.filename: 2-Bastion-000000052B9F.0B2-(quizzical beep).mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-000000055591.0B2-When I gazed into the iris, I found a great nothingness... it changed me. You must have experienced th.mp3

lines.speaker: Tracer
lines.filename: 2-Tracer-0000000550C0.0B2-That is not what I saw.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-000000055589.0B2-I do not sense the spark of life within you.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-00000005B805.0B2-Why do you think that is_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-0000000555A4.0B2-Some believe that the full moon is a good omen.mp3

lines.speaker: Cassidy
lines.filename: 2-Cassidy-000000054FE1.0B2-Maybe if you're a werewolf.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-00000005559D.0B2-When did you receive this curse, countess_.mp3

lines.speaker: Widowmaker
lines.filename: 2-Widowmaker-00000005B80C.0B2-It is no curse.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-00000005559B.0B2-You blame yourself for the dragons' reign of terror... but it is not your fault.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-00000005556A.0B2-You weren't there, monk. You don't know about my failure.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-00000005559A.0B2-Rarely has my path crossed a warrior as cheerful as you.mp3

lines.speaker: Torbjörn
lines.filename: 2-Torbjörn-00000005555C.0B2-When you've seen as much as I have, either you laugh or you go mad.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-000000055599.0B2-A pause in the battle. An opportunity to recenter our minds.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-0000000550E0.0B2-I am centered.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-000000055598.0B2-Take care that you do not spend yourself before the battle is done!.mp3

lines.speaker: Genji
lines.filename: 2-Genji-0000000550DF.0B2-I am only just getting started.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-00000005F116.0B2-There is much to admire about a rebellious spirit. Questioning tradition is how new tradition is forme.mp3

lines.speaker: D.Va
lines.filename: 2-D.Va-00000005F125.0B2-Oh, that's good! I'll use that the next time Sojourn gives me trouble.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-0000000635E6.0B2-I sense that your hardest battle is yet to come.mp3

lines.speaker: Hanzo
lines.filename: 2-Hanzo-0000000630E0.0B2-Hmph. I will best any enemy, no matter how strong.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 3-Zenyatta-0000000635E7.0B2-And what of the enemy within_.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-0000000635EB.0B2-Seeking progress by sowing chaos is like planting a tree in a volcano.mp3

lines.speaker: Doomfist
lines.filename: 2-Doomfist-00000006447A.0B2-Exactly.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-0000000635EC.0B2-Those who seek only to enrich themselves live the most impoverished lives of all.mp3

lines.speaker: Roadhog
lines.filename: 2-Roadhog-000000063DC5.0B2-(sigh).mp3

lines.speaker: Junkrat
lines.filename: 3-Junkrat-000000063D63.0B2-That's why I'm an artist.mp3

lines.speaker: Ashe
lines.filename: 4-Ashe-000000063D29.0B2-Yeah_ And those who seek my wrath tend to find it.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-0000000635F0.0B2-I have always wondered what it is like being inside an orb.mp3

lines.speaker: Wrecking Ball
lines.filename: 2-Wrecking Ball-000000063959.0B2-(hamster noises) He says, _Don't even think about it._.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-0000000635F3.0B2-You spend your second chance at life walking a lonely road.mp3

lines.speaker: Reaper
lines.filename: 2-Reaper-00000006384B.0B2-No one cares, monk.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 3-Zenyatta-0000000635F4.0B2-Someone always cares. You must simply seek them out.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-0000000635F5.0B2-You have an intense gaze, Doctor.mp3

lines.speaker: Moira
lines.filename: 2-Moira-000000064419.0B2-I am thinking on how best to utilize you.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 3-Zenyatta-0000000635F6.0B2-In the coming battle, you mean_.mp3

lines.speaker: Moira
lines.filename: 4-Moira-00000006441E.0B2-Perhaps.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-0000000658DC.0B2-There is a new sadness in you, brother.mp3

lines.speaker: Ramattra
lines.filename: 2-Ramattra-000000063FEB.0B2-No. I've simply grown tired of pretending I am content.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 3-Zenyatta-0000000658DB.0B2-Perhaps I can share your burden.mp3

lines.speaker: Ramattra
lines.filename: 4-Ramattra-000000063FED.0B2-You already do.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-0000000658E0.0B2-It is often those with the loudest voice who have the most to lose.mp3

lines.speaker: Mauga
lines.filename: 2-Mauga-00000006783D.0B2-Good thing I always win!.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 1-Zenyatta-000000068626.0B2-True strength comes to those who accept their weaknesses.mp3

lines.speaker: Illari
lines.filename: 2-Illari-000000066DAE.0B2-That's not what I was taught.mp3

lines.speaker: Zenyatta
lines.filename: 3-Zenyatta-000000068628.0B2-But it is never too late to learn.mp3

lines.speaker: Zeus
lines.filename: 1-Zeus-0000000656DA.0B2-The Battle for Olympus is complete!.mp3

lines.speaker: Zeus
lines.filename: 2-Zeus-0000000656D9.0B2-Our champion will be immortalized in stone for all eternity.mp3
